        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 6:16PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Haynes, or near Palestine, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forrest City, Marianna, Hughes, Madison, Caldwell, Colt, Widener,
Moro, Rondo, Aubrey, Haynes, Brickeys, New Salem, New Home, Lagrange,
Cody, Cottonwood Corner, Haleside, New Castle, and Soudan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
